### 9. Plaintext Key Names in Audit Log (Medium)

> [!WARNING]
> The audit log stores variable key names (`key TEXT`) in **unencrypted plaintext**.

- **File**: [vault_db.rs](file:///D:/github/varlock_ui/src-tauri/src/vault/vault_db.rs#L416-L421) and [audit.rs](file:///D:/github/varlock_ui/src-tauri/src/vault/audit.rs)
- **Issue**: The main `variables` table correctly hashes key names with SHA-256 for metadata protection. But the `access_log` table stores the raw key name in plain text (e.g., `"API_KEY"`, `"DATABASE_URL"`). An attacker with DB file access can enumerate all variable names ever accessed.
- **Recommendation**: Either hash the key name in audit logs using the same `key_hash()` function, or encrypt the entire audit log, or make the `key` column store the hash instead.

